My parents were most involved in politics and have shared with Riigikogu members their interest in today's Kyrgyzstan. Hopefully they can enjoy your visit and the fruits of your hard work in improving relations between the 2 countries in the future.”

Maijaliisa Johanna Tupits, student Minister Riigikogu

“Many years have passed since the wars in our region.

It is very important to see young people who are interested in the situation in neighbouring countries, so that they could contribute the development of more intensive relations between Estonia and Kyrgyzstan and organisations who work on behalf of our countries.”

Laura Pirko

“A few years ago I was involved in youth diplomacy here in Estonia and around the world. This was a very broad way to get acquainted with different cultures and traditions, to broaden one's horizons, to share information with our politicians and diplomats, and to shape opinion among our modern youth. Youth diplomacy is a very interesting and positive process, when people from different countries and cultures work together for a common goal. I am glad that the Riigikogu has stepped forward and organised such an interesting project here. I am happy that Estonia has accepted this important task in the region and will participate in organising the events during the visit of the Kyrgyzstan delegation to Estonia.”

Irina Jakovlev
